class.description:
[PuertsEnvironment] owns one live scripting runtime created from a backend resource such as [PuertsV8Backend], [PuertsNodejsBackend], [PuertsQuickjsBackend], or [PuertsLuaBackend]. Call [method initialize] before using the environment. The environment installs global helpers [code]load_type()[/code], [code]log_error()[/code], [code]log_warn()[/code], and [code]log_info()[/code].
The [method initialize] call requires a [PuertsStringNameCachePool]. You can share one pool across multiple environments, or use different pool instances (and policies) per environment.
Values returned from [method eval] and [method get_global] stay wrapped as [PuertsScriptValue] objects. This keeps object references alive across the script boundary and lets you inspect or convert them later. Calling [method dispose] releases the runtime and invalidates every [PuertsScriptValue] created by this environment.
[codeblocks]
[gdscript]
var backend := PuertsV8Backend.new()
var env := PuertsEnvironment.new()

var pool := PuertsStringNameCachePool.new()
pool.initialize(PuertsStringNameCachePool.POLICY_HASH_MAP, 512)
var err := env.initialize(backend, pool)
if err != OK:
    return

env.eval("globalThis.answer = 40 + 2")
var answer := env.get_global("answer").to_int()
print(answer) # 42
[/gdscript]
[/codeblocks]
